content.text: HTML Unordered Lists
The HTML <ul> tag defines an unordered (bulleted) list.
content.html: The HTML <ul> tag defines an unordered (bulleted) list.

content.text: Unordered HTML List
An unordered list starts with the <ul> tag. Each list item starts with the <li> tag.
content.html: An unordered list starts with the <ul> tag. Each list item starts with the <li> tag.

content.text: The list items will be marked with bullets (small black circles) by default:
content.html: The list items will be marked with bullets (small black circles) by default:

content.code_html:
<ul>
  <li>Coffee</li>
  <li>Tea</li>
  <li>Milk</li>
</ul>

content.text: Unordered HTML List - Choose List Item Marker
The CSS list-style-type property is used to define the style of the list item marker. It can have one of the following values:
content.html: The CSS list-style-type property is used to define the style of the list item marker. It can have one of the following values:

content.code_html:
Value Description
disc Sets the list item marker to a bullet (default)
circle Sets the list item marker to a circle
square Sets the list item marker to a square
none The list items will not be marked

content.text: Disc

content.code_html:
<ul style="list-style-type:disc;">
  <li>Coffee</li>
  <li>Tea</li>
  <li>Milk</li>
</ul>

content.text: Circle

content.code_html:
<ul style="list-style-type:circle;">
  <li>Coffee</li>
  <li>Tea</li>
  <li>Milk</li>
</ul>

content.text: Square

content.code_html:
<ul style="list-style-type:square;">
  <li>Coffee</li>
  <li>Tea</li>
  <li>Milk</li>
</ul>

content.text: No List Marker

content.code_html:
<ul style="list-style-type:none;">
  <li>Coffee</li>
  <li>Tea</li>
  <li>Milk</li>
</ul>

content.text: Nested HTML Lists
Lists can be nested (list inside list):

content.code_html:
<ul>
  <li>Coffee</li>
  <li>Tea
    <ul>
      <li>Black tea</li>
      <li>Green tea</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Milk</li>
</ul>

content.text: Note: A list item ( <li> ) can contain a new list, and other HTML elements, like images and links, etc.
content.html: Note: A list item (<li>) can contain a new list, and other HTML elements, like images and links, etc.

content.text: Horizontal List with CSS
HTML lists can be styled in many different ways with CSS.
content.html: HTML lists can be styled in many different ways with CSS.

content.text: One popular way is to style a list horizontally, to create a navigation menu:

syntax_highlighting.text:
list-style-type: none;
    margin: 0;  padding: 0;  overflow: hidden;  background-color: #333333;
display: block;  color: white;  text-align: center;  padding: 16px;  text-decoration: none;

content.code_html:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<style>
ul {
  list-style-type: none;
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
  overflow: hidden;
  background-color: #333333;
}

li {
  float: left;
}

li a {
  display: block;
  color: white;
  text-align: center;
  padding: 16px;
  text-decoration: none;
}

li a:hover {
  background-color: #111111;
}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<ul>
  <li><a href="#home">Home</a></li>
  <li><a href="#news">News</a></li>
  <li><a href="#contact">Contact</a></li>
  <li><a href="#about">About</a></li>
</ul>

</body>
</html>

content.text: HTML List Tags

content.code_html:
Tag Description
<ul> Defines an unordered list
<ol> Defines an ordered list
<li> Defines a list item
<dl> Defines a description list
<dt> Defines a term in a description list
<dd> Describes the term in a description list
